children.text: The perimeters of the ceiling in almost all areas has not been properly trimmed for perimeter fixings at 300mm centres to prevent the ceiling from failure.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .
The plasterboard manufacturer in their installation instructions state in the ‘Fixing to Ceilings’ section that
‘It is recommended that at sheet ends screws are spaced at 300mm maximum centres for cornices and 150mm maximum centres for square set finish’
The builder must install additional trimmers throughout to allow the plasterboard to be fixed at 300mm centres along the trimmers, in accordance with the manufacturer’s requirements.
